org.mxupdate.plugin
Class Export_mxJPO

java.lang.Object
  org.mxupdate.plugin.AbstractPlugin_mxJPO
      org.mxupdate.plugin.Export_mxJPO

 class Export_mxJPO
extends AbstractPlugin_mxJPO

The JPO class is the plug-in to export configuration items (administration objects) or in other words with the class the TCL update file could be created depending on the configuration item type (administration type).

Export_mxJPO

Method Detail

execute

Map<String,?> execute(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      Map<String,Object> _arguments)

All given administration objects are exported and the related update file is returned. The administration objects to export in _args are identified by the administration type (see TypeDef_mxJPO) and the MX names of the administration objects.

The _arguments differs between two different possible modes. The first possibility depends on the file name with the argument key

  • ARGUMENT_KEY_FILENAME: name of the file to export
The second possibility depends on the type definition and the name of the configuration item with the argument keys
  • ARGUMENT_KEY_TYPEDEF: type definition
  • ARGUMENT_KEY_NAME: name of the configuration item

The returned packed values (packed with method AbstractPlugin_mxJPO.prepareReturn(String, String, Exception, Object)) includes the logging messages itself and for configuration item type a map with exporting information. The exporting information map defines four keys:

  • RETURN_KEY_TYPEDEF: type definition of the configuration item
  • RETURN_KEY_NAME: name of the configuration item
  • RETURN_KEY_PATH: path within the file directory of the configuration item (without file name)
  • RETURN_KEY_CODE: TCL update source code of the configuration item
  • RETURN_KEY_FILENAME: file name of the configuration item

If an exception is thrown the exception is packed in the returned map.

Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache with the MX context
_arguments - map with all search arguments
Returns:
packed return values in maps
See Also:
